<section class="certification-section">
    <h2>EcoSawit+ Certification</h2>
    <p>The EcoSawit+ Certification represents the gold standard in sustainable palm oil production. Designed to align with global benchmarks such as the EU Deforestation Regulation (EUDR) and RSPO standards, our certification empowers Indonesian farmers while ensuring the highest levels of environmental stewardship and traceability.</p>
    
    <h3>Why Choose EcoSawit+ Certification?</h3>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Comprehensive Compliance:</strong> Meets and exceeds global sustainability standards, ensuring access to premium markets.</li>
        <li><strong>Advanced Traceability:</strong> Blockchain and satellite-based monitoring ensure full transparency from farm to market.</li>
        <li><strong>Empowered Farmers:</strong> Provides training, resources, and financial incentives to support sustainable practices and improve livelihoods.</li>
        <li><strong>Regenerative Practices:</strong> Focuses on restoring ecosystems, improving biodiversity, and promoting carbon sequestration.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>The Certification Process</h3>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Pre-Application Phase:</strong> Farmers or companies express interest. Eligibility is screened by the Palm Eco Alliance team.</li>
        <li><strong>On-the-Ground GIS Assessment:</strong> Data collection evaluates land-use, farming practices, and carbon sequestration potential.</li>
        <li><strong>Satellite Verification:</strong> Independent satellite monitoring verifies land-use claims and ensures deforestation-free practices.</li>
        <li><strong>Audit and Reporting:</strong> A comprehensive report is prepared, recommending certification or corrective actions.</li>
        <li><strong>Certification Decision:</strong> Certification is issued to compliant entities, while others are provided a roadmap for improvement.</li>
        <li><strong>Market Access and Branding:</strong> Certified producers gain access to premium buyers and can use the EcoSawit+ label.</li>
        <li><strong>Continuous Monitoring:</strong> Annual satellite tracing and periodic reassessments ensure ongoing compliance.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>EcoSawit+ Certification Process Flowchart</h3>
    <div class="flowchart">
        <div class="node">Pre-Application Phase<br>- Express interest<br>- Eligibility screening</div>
        <div class="arrow">↓</div>
        <div class="node">On-the-Ground GIS Assessment<br>- Data collection<br>- Compliance guidance</div>
        <div class="arrow">↓</div>
        <div class="node">Satellite Verification<br>- Validate land-use claims<br>- Identify discrepancies</div>
        <div class="arrow">↓</div>
        <div class="node">Audit and Reporting<br>- Joint report<br>- Recommendations</div>
        <div class="arrow">↓</div>
        <div class="node">Certification Decision<br>- Issue certification<br>- Provide roadmap</div>
        <div class="arrow">↓</div>
        <div class="node">Market Access and Branding<br>- Use EcoSawit+ Label<br>- Access premium buyers</div>
        <div class="arrow">↓</div>
        <div class="node">Continuous Monitoring<br>- Annual tracing<br>- Bi-annual reassessments</div>
    </div>
</section>

